<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5315438>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Identification characters of Harmothoe impar, H. clavigera, H. rarispina, H. extenuata, H. fragilis, H. vesiculosa, H. abyssicola, and H. mariannae n. sp." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5315438/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5315446>
    dc:description "FIGURE 6. Harmothoe abyssicola (syntype, af with everted pharynx, ZMO C2030). (A) anterior end; styles of median antenna, left dorsal tentacular cirrus, and left dorsal cirrus missing; everted pharynx not figured; (B) right middle elytron from unknown segment, free in vial; (C) micro- and macrotubercles from same; (D) right cirrigerous parapodium from unknown segment, free in vial, posterior view, style of ventral cirrus missing; (E) short notochaeta; (F) long notochaeta; (G) tip of same; (H) middle neurochaeta; (I) tip of same; (J) tip of unidentate upper neurochaeta; (K) tip of bidentate upper neurochaeta; (L) distal part of lower neurochaeta. (Scales: A, B = 1 mm; C = 100 µm; D = 500 µm; E, F, H = 250 µm; G, I–L = 50 µm)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5315446/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

